        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:43PM EDT by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL</headline>
        <description>At 442 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms near
Ona, or 10 miles southwest of Wauchula, moving north at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Limestone, Zolfo Springs, and Ona.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
